<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-185DF587-7FB8-49A8-8BF3-626091680E7F" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-185DF587-7FB8-49A8-8BF3-626091680E7F" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">19 Print and wind without a tension bar</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-6F742A58-1849-43D8-8AA4-BABD15C27E2A"><p class="- topic/p ">Winding media without a tension bar, loose winding, is used for most media that can be transported well and is not too weak. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-8A380DA4-9A3D-4942-A1E4-3FDCFD6532DB" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul id="UL_B5A4DF99AE1444DAADEEEFA23632434A" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_4D1FBBA8C9EE4F15B1DA63BFC6C1280B" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The use of the tension bar is set in the media type configuration in the RIP software. For winding without a tension bar you must select <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">no tension bar</uicontrol></ph> under <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Winding tension</uicontrol></ph>. 
</p></li><li id="LI_7EDD718158EF4A1E980DD19CC7D8A2DC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure you have loaded a take-up roll on the roll winder. For more information, see 
<xref keyref="19FUNC020" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-56716598-C571-4F19-B3B1-E4574A3E542C.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 19 Load a take-up roll core onto the roll winder?>19 Load a take-up roll core onto the roll winder</xref>. 
</p></li><li id="LI_79DD8A093D5849B68E2619B4F77C683F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer is ready to print. 
</p></li></ul><note type="important" id="GUID-9CBCE980-D5D7-4038-B333-510B4ACAF316" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Use the stop switch, to stop the winder immediately. Do not forget to switch it on again. 
</p><fig id="FIG_BB762A18489D4FD480D644767835EAEC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-675D0A0B-D259-48EB-9C75-AE9FF6D4CA34-low.png" id="IMAGE_B498352E7DE64FFDB428002CCB1BCBDD" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-675D0A0B-D259-48EB-9C75-AE9FF6D4CA34-low.png"/></fig></note></prereq><steps id="GUID-9085D37B-CB1D-45D4-BF66-FF101E474392" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step id="STEP_6DC11A1C61FA40B1BE34D52CC7EE3CF3" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel tap on the <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Output</text></uicontrol></ph> icon. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_2BF18C6C01B44B1C810A0B5D06861661" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Make sure <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Wind the output</text></uicontrol></ph> is set to <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Yes</text></uicontrol></ph>. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_2145034036F540BABDFDD2E9B3A069CE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-228855AB-307C-4AB9-9ACF-4F2B9D48FD36-low.png" id="IMAGE_4F94CAAE8315487F9AB61DAB76F2F262" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-228855AB-307C-4AB9-9ACF-4F2B9D48FD36-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_CD132A4E8144424AB15786C3D7BCA08A" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Start a print job. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer will continue printing. The clamp closes when the media reaches the tape position, and the operator panel gives a message indicating you can tape the media. 
</p></info></step><step id="STEP_FB773BD273684E6B813C5A9F96885DE0" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Make sure the media guides are out of the way as they can damage the media. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "/><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_3E11EB6A0BCE44A197DF6B1716BE8C27" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-205B7A15-97F3-4CEE-8427-BC73FA41E6AD-low.png" id="IMAGE_2296EF9D63C046658DF5430A74E36896" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-205B7A15-97F3-4CEE-8427-BC73FA41E6AD-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_B58C8E59547F430CAE6BA842D19C14C3" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Take the leading edge of the media and align it on the core. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_99BC92FF027942278DA3941240CF0B08" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tape first the center and then the sides of the media to the core. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_BFA0E13EFF68451DB7579627C2153F8E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-898064C1-D114-4FBB-848C-40381A1A5144-low.png" id="IMAGE_97EE0D5E0A3E4CE39EEE56E70EE29388" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-898064C1-D114-4FBB-848C-40381A1A5144-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_412D0029A7794099A36C202F264C330D" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Move the media guides towards the middle to align with the media. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_64FDA630AE214128ABF031F054FEDE2D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C2DCA7BA-D7A7-4DBF-8CE2-A090F481401A-low.png" id="IMAGE_6D8F0A28D82B4462956BCD98563D3D18" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C2DCA7BA-D7A7-4DBF-8CE2-A090F481401A-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_4E812DA9922F45F888C6E6D1F6D91FDB" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Ready</text></uicontrol></ph>. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer continues printing while winding the job. 
</p></info></step></steps><postreq id="GUID-91479708-15B5-42A2-AD33-B1A0914EA508" class="- topic/section task/postreq "><p class="- topic/p ">When you want to stop winding you have to cut the media. 
</p></postreq></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-77E3E148-DF16-4838-9432-CE905B393B0C.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
